  coreConcepts.MetricSpace<T>

All Implemented Interfaces:
DataSet<T>, Metric<T>, java.lang.Iterable<T>
public class MetricSpace<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements DataSet<T>, Metric<T>

Author:
Richard Connor This class simulates multiple inheritence from an instance of a DataSet and a Metric to provide a metric space implemenations. It adds no functionality and simply delegates method calls to the appropriate object used at construction.

randomValue

public T randomValue()
Specified by:
randomValue in interface DataSet<T>
Returns:
a random value from the set. If the set is eg read from a pre-randomised file, this may be implemented as just the next value. It is good practice for classes implementing this to give repeated streams of values from successive calls for each instance creation, to allow experiments to be reliably repeated. If this behaviour is not desirable for a given task, then this should be explicitly built into the constructor.
